"source": [
"### 1. Data Selection & Preprocessing\n",
"Given the size of the dataset (10GB+), we use a focused subset. We incorporate language filtering and administrative noise removal to ensure the quality of discovered patterns.\n",
"\n",
"Key Preprocessing Steps:\n",
"- Language Filtering: Using langid to retain English-only records.\n",
"- Tag Cleaning: Stripping administrative shelves (e.g., 'to-read', 'owned', 'kindle') that provide high support but low discovery value."
]
},
{
"cell_type": "code",
"execution_count": null,
"metadata": {},
"outputs": [],
"source": [
"import pandas as pd\n",
"import seaborn as sns\n",
"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
"import sys\n",
"import os\n",
"import gc\n",
"\n",
"# Add scripts directory to path for custom modules\n",
"sys.path.append(os.path.abspath('../scripts'))\n",
"from association import run_association_mining\n",
"\n",
"# Aesthetic settings for EDA\n",
"sns.set_theme(style="whitegrid")\n",
"plt.rcParams['figure.figsize'] = [12, 6]\n",
"\n",
"print("Environment initialized and libraries loaded.")"
]
},
{
"cell_type": "markdown",
"metadata": {},
"source": [
"### 2. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)\n",
"We investigate the basic distributions of our Romantasy subset. This intuition helps define the thresholds for our mining algorithms."
]
},
{
"cell_type": "code",
"execution_count": null,
"metadata": {},
"outputs": [],
"source": [
"# Loading the filtered Romantasy metadata\n",
"df_books = pd.read_json('../data/romantasy_books_subset.json', lines=True)\n",
"\n",
"# Visualization 1: Rating Distribution\n",
"sns.histplot(df_books['average_rating'], bins=30, kde=True, color='teal')\n",
"plt.title('Distribution of Average Ratings: Romantasy Subset')\n",
"plt.show()\n",
"\n",
"# Visualization 2: Most Frequent Cleaned Shelves\n",
"all_shelves = []\n",
"for shelves in df_books['popular_shelves']:\n",
"    for s in shelves:\n",
"        # Basic thresholding to find meaningful tags\n",
"        if int(s['count']) > 20:\n",
"            all_shelves.append(s['name'])\n",
"\n",
"# Filtering out noise manually for EDA overview\n",
"noise = ['to-read', 'favorites', 'owned', 'currently-reading', 'kindle', 'books-i-own', 'ebook']\n",
"filtered_tags = [t for t in all_shelves if t.lower() not in noise]\n",
"\n",
"pd.Series(filtered_tags).value_counts().head(20).plot(kind='barh', color='purple')\n",
"plt.title('Top 20 Discovered Literary Tags (Post-Cleaning)')\n",
"plt.gca().invert_yaxis()\n",
"plt.show()"
]
},
{
"cell_type": "markdown",
"metadata": {},
"source": [
"### 3. Discovery Question 1: Association Rule Mining (FP-Growth)\n",
"We investigate the hidden associations between genres. We are particularly interested in seeing how 'Romantasy' bridges traditional 'Fantasy' and 'Romance' niches."
]
},
{
"cell_type": "code",
"execution_count": null,
"metadata": {},
"outputs": [],
"source": [
"# Mining the transaction file generated by our extraction script\n",
"itemsets, rules = run_association_mining('../data/romantasy.csv', min_support=0.08, min_threshold=1.5)\n",
"\n",
"if rules is not None:\n",
"    # Displaying rules with the highest Lift\n",
"    display(rules[['antecedents', 'consequents', 'support', 'confidence', 'lift']].head(10))\n",
"else:\n",
"    print("No rules found. Adjust support thresholds.")"
]
},
