"### 4. Preliminary Findings & Interpretation\n",
"Initial Insights:\n",
"1. Genre Overlap: A high Lift (9.42) between ya-fiction and ya-fantasy confirms a dominant Young Adult presence in the 2017 Romantasy data. \n",
"2. Helpfulness Patterns: Highly-voted reviews tend to correlate with longer character counts, which we will verify using multivariate analysis in the next phase.\n",
"3. Reader Personas: The wide spread in average_rating (centered around 4.0 but with a significant tail) provides a good foundation for K-Means clustering in M3 to separate 'Casual' vs 'Critical' readers."
]
